headline: Wall Street Favors Vanilla Options Rather Than VIX to Hedge
summary: With signs of generally extended positioning within equities, investors are debating the most effective way to protect gains before Nvidia Corp. earnings, jobs and inflation data and the Fed rate decision.  With the market still in “buy-the-dip” mode, many strategists are touting S&P 500 Index put spreads and, more recently, look-back or resettable puts that will be useful should markets continue grinding higher in the short term.  “Vanilla puts or put spreads on the SPX may be a more reliable hedge given the current market regime,” said Tanvir Sandhu, chief global derivatives strategist at Bloomberg Intelligence.

headline: What to watch in Nvidia earnings: China, H20, chip sales, outlook
summary: Asking for a Trend host Josh Lipton outlines the three biggest things for investors to look for in Nvidia's (NVDA) earnings report this week. The company's second quarter results will be out on Wednesday, Aug. 27 after markets close. Analysts expect a strong report from Nvidia, driven by healthy demand, while the company's China sales will also be in focus after the Information reported that the company called for a halt to production of its H20 chips. Investors also await Nvidia's forecast for the rest of the year and for the third quarter. Tune in to Yahoo Finance on Wednesday, Aug. 27 at 4 p.m. for special coverage of Nvidia's quarterly results. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Asking for a Trend.
